metadata.name: Vents #568
metadata.description:
Near the start of December @Studio Yorktown launched his "Studio Yorktown Color Town Hall" library of wonderful colour palettes.

"You know what this Town Hall needs?" I asked no one in particular, "Vents!". Besides, what's more Christmassy than a good old vent?

Some nice soothing gradients, with a selection of innies and outies, structure, form, and sometimes sharp edges. I humbly suggest aiming to get a set of three üòÅ

Thank you for everything fxhash in 2022, looking forwards to 2023!

READ MORE: https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/vents

INSTRUCTIONS ::

h - Toggle high-res
n - toggle noise on/off
s - Download and save image

PRINTING INSTRUCTIONS ::

High-res will output a 8,192 x 8,192 image, at 300dpi it should print at...

27.3 x 27.3 inches
69.3 x 69.3 cm

metadata.name: Computing memory #103
metadata.description:
This creation takes Penghu, Taiwan, my hometown as the theme, and uses the style of expired films to reconstruct the scene in my memory.
During the creative process, I think about how "mechanism" and "choice" affect the scene in my memory, I also asked myself in the process of creation, did I discover the appearance left in my memory after this work or was it the appearance I hoped to see?

2023 shengkai

metadata.name: To Exist and Be There #45
metadata.description:
This piece was inspired by the personal thought of life and the realization of why we as humans exist within the world. The diversity it contained and how everything accumulated may affect each other. It might be unanswered, but those things existed and stayed there, thus being there for us to configure.

May kindness and safety always stay with us.

/////INTERACTIVITY/////
Do all the instructions below after opening the live mode.

1. To capture the screen, press the "c" button on your computer keyboard.

2. To save a 2-second .GIF from your iteration, press the "s" button on your computer keyboard. Please be patient while waiting for the piece to save and render its frames.

3. To adjust the piece resolution, you need to set your browser first and then reload the browser every time you want to capture the screen or save the rendered .GIF file.
///////////////////////

Created using Hydra and p5.js

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2022
https://linktr.ee/ranggapuraji

metadata.name: Sketch Book #49
metadata.description:
Sketch Book is a generative collection that imagines an abstract sketch built with lines and shapes in harmony with each other.

It‚Äôs called Sketch Book as it started with me sketching a bunch of lines in p5.js and then warping them to give them a natural waviness. The artwork combines subdivision and domain warping techniques before drawing the final lines and shapes on the canvas. 

Sketch Book renders as a fixed resolution output (1000x1200px). Controls (in live view): 

Press [2] to render at 2000x2400px
Press [4] to render at 4000x4800px
Press [8] to render at 8000x9600px
Press [s] to save the current view (default or higher resolution image)
